s==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [https://www.google.com/books/edition/U_S_Army_Patches_Flashes_and_Ovals/KKKCGwAACAAJ?hl=en U.S. Army Patches, Flashes, and Ovals: An Illustrated Encyclopedia of Cloth Unit Insignia], by Barry Jason Stein, dated 2007, {{ISBN|9780979161308}}\n\n{{US Army uniforms}}\n{{US Army navbox}}\n{{US Air Force navbox}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:United States Military Beret Flash}}\n[[Category:Heraldry of the United States Army]]\n", "name_user": "McChizzle", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eUS Air Force:Minor image description edit", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_military_beret_flash"}
{"title_page": "Rodin Deprem", "text_new": "{{short description|Swedish footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Rodin Deprem\n| fullname = \n| image = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1998|5|23}}\n| birth_place = [[G\u00e4vle]], Sweden\n| height = 1.77m<ref>{{worldfootball.net|rodin-deprem/}}</ref>\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth II|Greuther F\u00fcrth II]]\n| clubnumber = \n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Rynninge IK]]\n| youthyears2 = \n| youthclubs2 = \n| youthyears3 = 2016\u20132017\n| youthclubs3 = [[\u00d6rebro SK]]\n| years1 = 2014\u20132016\n| clubs1 = [[Rynninge IK]]\n| caps1 = 42\n| goals1 = 5\n| years2 = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs2 = [[\u00d6rebro SK]]\n| caps2 = 13\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2020\u2013\n| clubs3 = [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth II|Greuther F\u00fcrth II]]\n| caps3 = 1\n| goals3 = 0\n| pcupdate = 15:01, 23 March 2020 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Rodin Deprem''' (born 23 May 1998) is a Swedish footballer who plays for German club [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth II]].<ref>{{Soccerway|rodin-deprem/542194}}</ref>\n\n==Youth career==\nRodin Deprem was born in G\u00e4vle.<ref>[https://www.totallyorebro.se/noje/rodin-deprem-ar-redo-for-nasta-sasong/ RODIN DEPREM \u00c4R REDO F\u00d6R N\u00c4STA S\u00c4SONG], totallyorebro.se, 25 November 2018</ref> When he was six years old the family moved to \u00d6rebro and Rodin started playing football in Rynninge IK. During his young teens Rodin performed well in the youth teams which resulted in the club giving him the chance to play in the [[Division 2 (Swedish football)|Swedish Division 2]] at the age of 16.<ref name=ft>[https://www.lagstatistik.se/player?playerId=45647 Rodin Deprem - Lagstatistik], lagstatistik.se</ref> Deprem left Rynninge to join [[\u00d6rebro SK]] in the summer of 2016 at the age of 18.<ref name=\"ft\" /> After an impressive period during 2017, he managed to set the record for most goals scored in the U19 Allsvenskan until date with 29 goals in 22 games. The season caught the eye of several clubs, and Deprem was even close to sign with Dutch club [[De Graafschap]] but the deal was stopped due the clubs disagreeing on the terms. After all Deprem signed a professional contract with \u00d6rebro SK and was promoted to the A-squad in March 2018.<ref>[https://fogis.se/information/?scr=scorers&ftid=66437 Skytteliga - U19 Allsvenskan Norra], fogis.se</ref><ref>[https://tonsser.com/se/blog/nextgen/tonaringen-slog-malrekord Ton\u00e5ringen slog m\u00e5lrekord], tonsser.com, 15 October 2017</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===\u00d6rebro SK===\nDuring his first season in [[Allsvenskan]], Deprem played 8 matches, of which 1 was from the start and 7 as a substitute. During his second season he played 5 matches, of which he started 2 and 3 as a substitute. After the 2019 season, Deprem left the club due to lack of playing time.<ref>[https://fotbolltransfers.com/site/news/115586 Officiellt: Lorentzson, Bark och Deprem l\u00e4mnar \u00d6rebro SK], fotbolltransfers.com, 1 November 2019</ref>\n\n===Greuther F\u00fcrth II===\nOn 16 February 2020 it was confirmed, that Deprem had joined the reserve team of [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth]].<ref>[https://fotbolltransfers.com/site/news/120098 Greuther F\u00fcrth uppges v\u00e4rva Rodin Deprem], fotbolltransfers.com, 16 February 2020</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Svenskfotboll|fid=626693}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Deprem, Rodin}}\n[[Category:Swedish people of Turkish descent]]\n[[Category:Swedish footballers]]\n[[Category:Swedish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Division 2 (Swedish football) players]]\n[[Category:Allsvenskan players]]\n[[Category:Regionalliga players]]\n[[Category:\u00d6rebro SK players]]\n[[Category:SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth II players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Swedish expatriate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Swedish footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Rodin Deprem\n| fullname    = \n| image       = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1998|5|23}}\n| birth_place = [[G\u00e4vle]], Sweden\n| height      = 1.78m<ref>{{worldfootball.net|rodin-deprem/}}</ref>\n| position    = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth II|Greuther F\u00fcrth II]]\n| clubnumber  = \n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Rynninge IK]]\n| youthyears2 = \n| youthclubs2 = Karlslund\n| youthyears3 = 2016\u20132017\n| youthclubs3 = [[\u00d6rebro SK]]\n| years1      = 2014\u20132016  | clubs1 = [[Rynninge IK]]                                 | caps1 = 42| goals1 = 5\n| years2      = 2018\u20132019  | clubs2 = [[\u00d6rebro SK]]                                   | caps2 = 13| goals2 = 0\n| years3      = 2020\u2013      | clubs3 = [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth II|Greuther F\u00fcrth II]]   | caps3 = 1 | goals3 = 0\n| pcupdate    = 15:01, 23 March 2020 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Rodin Deprem''' (born 23 May 1998) is a Swedish footballer who plays for German club [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth II]].<ref>{{Soccerway|rodin-deprem/542194}}</ref>\n\n==Youth career==\nRodin Deprem was born in G\u00e4vle.<ref>[https://www.totallyorebro.se/noje/rodin-deprem-ar-redo-for-nasta-sasong/ RODIN DEPREM \u00c4R REDO F\u00d6R N\u00c4STA S\u00c4SONG], totallyorebro.se, 25 November 2018</ref> When he was six years old the family moved to \u00d6rebro and Rodin started playing football in Rynninge IK. In his younger teens Rodin changed his club to Karlslund for a couple of seasons but he returned to Rynninge when the club gave him the chance to play in the [[Division 2 (Swedish football)|Swedish Division 2]] at the age of 16.<ref name=ft>[https://www.lagstatistik.se/player?playerId=45647 Rodin Deprem - Lagstatistik], lagstatistik.se</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===\u00d6rebro SK===\nDeprem left Rynninge to join [[\u00d6rebro SK]] in 2016 at the age of 18.<ref name=ft/> After an impressive period and during the 2017 season set the record for most goals scored in the U19 Allsvenskan with 29 goals in 22 games, he was promoted to the A-squad in 2018.<ref>[https://fogis.se/information/?scr=scorers&ftid=66437 Skytteliga - U19 Allsvenskan Norra], fogis.se</ref><ref>[https://tonsser.com/se/blog/nextgen/tonaringen-slog-malrekord Ton\u00e5ringen slog m\u00e5lrekord], tonsser.com, 15 October 2017</ref> During his first season in [[Allsvenskan]], Deprem played 8 matches, of which 1 was from the start and 7 as a substitute. During his second season he played 5 matches, of which he started 2 and 3 as a substitute. After the 2019 season, Deprem left the club due to lack of playing time.<ref>[https://fotbolltransfers.com/site/news/115586 Officiellt: Lorentzson, Bark och Deprem l\u00e4mnar \u00d6rebro SK], fotbolltransfers.com, 1 November 2019</ref>\n\n===Greuther F\u00fcrth II===\nOn 16 February 2020 it was confirmed, that Deprem had joined the reserve team of [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth]].<ref>[https://fotbolltransfers.com/site/news/120098 Greuther F\u00fcrth uppges v\u00e4rva Rodin Deprem], fotbolltransfers.com, 16 February 2020</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Svenskfotboll|fid=626693}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Deprem, Rodin}}\n[[Category:Swedish people of Turkish descent]]\n[[Category:Swedish footballers]]\n[[Category:Swedish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Division 2 (Swedish football) players]]\n[[Category:Allsvenskan players]]\n[[Category:Regionalliga players]]\n[[Category:\u00d6rebro SK players]]\n[[Category:SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth II players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Swedish expatriate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n", "name_user": "AllsvenskStatistik", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rodin_Deprem"}
{"title_page": "List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes", "text_new": "{{use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' episodes}}\n''[[The Amazing World of Gumball]]'' is a British-American [[cartoon series|animated]] [[television comedy|comedy]] television series created by [[Ben Bocquelet]] for [[Cartoon Network]];<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/the-amazing-world-of-gumball/episodes-season-1/325519 |title=The Amazing World of Gumball Season 1 episodes |magazine=[[TV Guide]] |accessdate=July 3, 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6HrO0zHKH?url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/the-amazing-world-of-gumball/episodes-season-1/325519 |archivedate=July 4, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> its [[The Amazing World of Gumball (season 6)|sixth season]] premiered on January 5, 2018. ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' revolves around the life of a 12-year-old cat named Gumball Watterson (Logan Grove, seasons 1 to 3; [[Jacob Hopkins]], season 3 to 5; Nicolas Cantu, rest of season 5 onwards) and his frequent shenanigans in the fictional American world of Elmore. Throughout the series, he interacts with characters such as his former pet, brother and best friend Darwin ([[Kwesi Boakye]], seasons 1 to 3; [[Terrell Ransom Jr.]], season 3 to 5; Donielle T. Hansley Jr, rest of season 5; Christian J. Simon, season 6 onwards), sister Anais (Kyla Rae Kowalewski), and parents Nicole and Richard ([[Teresa Gallagher]] and Dan Russell).\n\nBocquelet conceived ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' in 2007 while working as a development artist for [[Cartoon Network Studios Europe]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.turner.com/press_kits_detail.cfm?item_id=1298&presskit_id=239&press_section_id=2584 |title=Ben Bocquelet |publisher=[[Turner Broadcasting System]] |accessdate=October 19, 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDYqShEW?url=http://news.turner.com/press_kits_detail.cfm?item_id=1298&presskit_id=239&press_section_id=2584 |archivedate=November 18, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Daswani 2013\">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.worldscreen.com/articles/display/40804|title=Ben Bocquelet & 'The Amazing World of Gumball'|magazine=TV Kids|publisher=[[Mipcom]]|date=October 2013|pages=370\u201371|last=Daswani|first=Mansha|accessdate=November 18, 2013|url-access=subscription }}</ref> Having been asked by the network to pitch an idea for a new series for [[Adult Swim]], he took sketches of several unused characters he had created for commercials and started developing a concept for a new series based on them.<ref name=\"Animation\">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/gumball-begins-reign-of-color |title=Gumball Begins Reign of Color |magazine=[[Animation (magazine)|Animation]] |date=May 29, 2011 |accessdate=July 4, 2013 |last=Zahed |first=Ramin |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDYtMqr8?url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/gumball-begins-reign-of-color/ |archivedate=November 18, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> As Cartoon Network was heavily interested in \"family and school shows\" at the time, Bocquelet decided to make the series a kid series called ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' which was a combination of both.<ref name=\"Daswani 2013\"/><ref name=\"Animation\"/> He pitched the series to Daniel Lennard, vice president of Original Series and Development at [[Turner Broadcasting System|Turner Broadcasting]], who was impressed by the series' premise and ultimately greenlit its production.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thechildrensmediaconference.com/sessions/bafta-presents-the-amazing-world-of-gumball |title=BAFTA Presents: The Amazing World of Gumball |publisher=The Children's Media Conference |date=July 5, 2012 |accessdate=July 4, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141019230840/http://www.thechildrensmediaconference.com/sessions/bafta-presents-the-amazing-world-of-gumball/ |archivedate=October 19, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> The first series to be greenlit by Cartoon Network Studios Europe,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://weblogs.variety.com/bltv/2011/05/cartoon-net-charms-with-clever-import-gumball.html |title=Cartoon Net Charms With Clever Import 'Gumball' |newspaper=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=May 3, 2011 |accessdate=October 19, 2013 |last=Lowry |first=Brian |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120527061324/http://weblogs.variety.com/bltv/2011/05/cartoon-net-charms-with-clever-import-gumball.html |archivedate=May 27, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> it first aired on May 3, 2011 with the episode \"The DVD\", which was watched by 2.120 million viewers in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2011/05/04/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tnt-rides-nba-doubleheader-154112/cable_20110503 |title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: TNT Rides NBA Doubleheader |publisher=[[The Futon Critic]] |date=May 4, 2011 |accessdate=July 3, 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDZ341Hd?url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2011/05/04/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tnt-rides-nba-doubleheader-154112/cable_20110503/ |archivedate=November 18, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn June 2, 2014, Cartoon Network announced that the series had been renewed a fourth and fifth season.<ref name=\"BarbaLachD'Amato2014\">{{cite press release | url=https://pressroom.turner.com/us/cartoon-network/amazing-world-gumball/cartoon-network-doubles-down-global-hit-series-amazing | title=Cartoon Network Doubles Down on Global Hit Series ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' | publisher=Turner Press Site | date=June 2, 2014 | accessdate=June 2, 2014 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140607000350/https://pressroom.turner.com/us/cartoon-network/amazing-world-gumball/cartoon-network-doubles-down-global-hit-series-amazing#.WYq8HCNOnJA | archive-date=June 7, 2014 | author1=Barba, Jessica | author2=Lach, Dawn | author3=D'Amato, Adrienne | location=Los Angeles and New York City}}</ref> Both seasons combined consisted of 40 eleven-minute episodes.<ref name=\"Marino2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.worldscreen.com/articles/display/2014-06-02-gumball-season-renewals |title=The Amazing World of Gumball Greenlit for 4th & 5th Seasons |publisher=World Screen |work=TV Kids |date=June 2, 2014 |accessdate=June 2, 2014 |author=Marino, Joel |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Q2kKYlJ6?url=http://www.worldscreen.com/articles/display/2014-06-02-gumball-season-renewals |archivedate=June 3, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn June 22, 2016, Cartoon Network renewed the series for a sixth season which would consist of 44 episodes.<ref name=\"awn.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.awn.com/news/amazing-world-gumball-renewed-season-six|title='Amazing World of Gumball' Renewed for Season Six|publisher=AWN|accessdate=July 5, 2016}}</ref> On September 6, 2016, [[Ben Bocquelet]] announced he would be departing production of ''Gumball'' upon completing the sixth season;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/benbocquelet/status/773562028489314309|title=Ben Bocquelet on Twitter|publisher=|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref> but production will continue without him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itechpost.com/articles/37923/20161008/the-amazing-world-of-gumball-creator-leaves-the-show-cartoon-network-to-continue-the-show-without-him.htm|title='Amazing World of Gumball' Creator Leaves The Show; Cartoon Network To Continue The Series Without Him?|first=iTech|last=Post|date=8 October 2016|publisher=|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref> However, on October 7, 2018, he retweeted an article stating that the sixth season will be the last. However, on October 2018, the author of that article made a follow up article clarifying that there could still be more seasons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regularcapital.com/2018/10/more-seasons-of-the-amazing-world-of-gumball-is-still-a-possiblity/|title=More Seasons Of The Amazing World Of Gumball Is Still A Possibility|website=RegularCapital|date=October 12, 2018}}</ref>\nThe series is rated [[TV-Y7-FV]] in the [[United States]] (and has a PG certificate in the UK on all DVD releases) for comedic fantasy violence, mild to moderate suggestive content (including use of sexual innuendo), rude (often dark) humor, and scenes of danger.<ref>{{cite web|title=TV Parental Control|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/legal/ratings.html|publisher=[[Cartoon Network]]|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\nLater in November 2019, a six-episode miniseries titled \u201cDarwin's Yearbook\u201d was announced.<ref name=anim />\n\n==Series overview==\n\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| color0S    = #1E5994\n| link0S     = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Pilot (2008-2016)\n| episodes0S = 1\n| linkT0S    = Pilot\n| start0S    = {{Start date|2008|5|9}}\n| ends0S     = {{End date|2016|3|5}}\n\n| color1     = #5EC5C4\n| link1      = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2011\u201312)\n| episodes1  = 36\n| start1     = {{Start date|2011|5|3}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2012|3|13}}\n\n| color2     = #EDCC26\n| link2      = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (2012\u201313)\n| episodes2  = 40\n| start2     = {{Start date|2012|8|7}}\n| end2       = {{End date|2013|12|3}}\n\n| color3     = #ACF16C\n| link3      = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 3 (2014\u201315)\n| episodes3  = 40\n| start3     = {{Start date|2014|6|5}}\n| end3       = {{End date|2015|8|6}}\n\n| color4     = #C869FB\n| link4      = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 4 (2015\u201316)\n| episodes4  = 40\n| start4     = {{Start date|2015|7|7}}\n| end4       = {{End date|2016|10|27}}\n\n| color5      = #FF5F5F\n| link5       = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 5 (2016\u201317)\n| episodes5   = 40\n| start5      = {{Start date|2016|9|1}}\n| end5        = {{End date|2017|11|10}}\n\n| color6      = #FFFF00\n| link6       = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 6 (2018\u201319)\n| episodes6   = 44\n| start6      = {{Start date|2018|1|5}}\n| end6        = {{End date|2019|6|24}}\n\n| color6S     = #F28500\n| link6S      = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Darwin's Yearbook (2019)\n| linkT6S     = ''Yearbook''\n| episodes6S  = 6\n| start6S     = {{Start date|2019|12|2}}\n| end6S       = {{End date|2019|12|6}}\n\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Episodes==\n\n===Pilot (2008)===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto;\"\n! style=\"background:#1E5994; color:white;\" scope=\"col\" width=25%| Title\n! style=\"background:#1E5994; color:white;\" scope=\"col\" width=40%| Written by\n! style=\"background:#1E5994; color:white;\" scope=\"col\" width=40%| Storyboarded by\n! style=\"background:#1E5994; color:white;\" scope=\"col\"| Date published\n|-\n{{Episode List\n|Title           = Early Reel\n|RTitle          = <ref name=\"Bocquelet 2013-01e-18\">{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CpbSqQ0CrjQ|title=Gumball 1min animation test|publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=January 18, 2013|accessdate=April 8, 2014|author=Bocquelet, Ben|authorlink=Ben Bocquelet}}</ref>\n|WrittenBy       = [[Ben Bocquelet]]\n|Aux2            = Sylvain Marc\n|OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2008|5|9}}\n|ShortSummary    = Prototype versions of Gumball and Darwin try to escape from school by building a [[Rube Goldberg machine]].\n|LineColor       = black\n}}\n|}\n\n===Season 1 (2011\u201312)===\n{{main|The Amazing World of Gumball (season 1)}}\n{{:The Amazing World of Gumball (season 1)}}\n\n===Season 2 (2012\u201313)===\n{{main|The Amazing World of Gumball (season 2)}}\n{{:The Amazing World of Gumball (season 2)}}\n\n===Season 3 (2014\u201315)===\n{{main|The Amazing World of Gumball (season 3)}}\n{{:The Amazing World of Gumball (season 3)}}\n\n===Season 4 (2015\u201316)===\n{{main|The Amazing World of Gumball (season 4)}}\n{{:The Amazing World of Gumball (season 4)}}\n\n===Season 5 (2016\u201317)===\n{{main|The Amazing World of Gumball (season 5)}}\n{{:The Amazing World of Gumball (season 5)}}\n\n===Season 6 (2018\u201319)===\n{{main|The Amazing World of Gumball (season 6)}}\n{{:The Amazing World of Gumball (season 6)}}\n\n==''Darwin's Yearbook'' (2019-2020)==\nA six-episode special called ''Darwin's Yearbook'' aired on Cartoon Network in December 2019. The miniseries features Darwin attempting to complete Elmore Junior High's yearbook by examining who he thinks should fill up the best spot. The miniseries is essentially a collection of [[clip show]] episodes.<ref name=anim>{{cite web|url=https://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/cn-brings-back-gumball-with-special-darwins-yearbook-episodes/|title=CN Brings Back 'Gumball' with Special \"Darwin's Yearbook\" Episodes|website=Animation Magazine|last=Milligan|first=Mercedes|date=November 4, 2019}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%;margin:auto;\"\n|- style=\"color:white\"\n! style=\"background:#F28500;color:black;\" width=5%|No. in<br />series\n! style=\"background:#F28500;color:black;\" width=12%|Title\n! style=\"background:#F28500;color:black;\" width=13%|U.S. air date\n! style=\"background:#F28500;color:black;\" width=10%|U.K. air date\n! style=\"background:#F28500;color:black;\" width=1%|Prod.<br />code\n! style=\"background:#F28500;color:black;\" width=1%|U.S. viewers<br />(millions)\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=1\n|Title=Banana Joe\n| RTitle={{Efn|name=yearbook1|This episode was first aired in France on December 7, 2019.}}\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|12|14}}\n|AltDate=December 2, 2019<ref>{{cite tweet|user=RegularTweetsUK|number=1191671077052862464|date=November 5, 2019|title=Thread: Official Confirmation from Cartoon Network UK: BRAND NEW: THE AMAZING WORLD O