sodes]]\n[[Category:Cartoon Network-related lists]]\n[[Category:2010s television-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' episodes}}\n''[[The Amazing World of Gumball]]'' is a British-American [[cartoon series|animated]] [[television comedy|comedy]] television series created by [[Ben Bocquelet]] for [[Cartoon Network]];<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/the-amazing-world-of-gumball/episodes-season-1/325519 |title=The Amazing World of Gumball Season 1 episodes |journal=[[TV Guide]] |accessdate=July 3, 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6HrO0zHKH?url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/the-amazing-world-of-gumball/episodes-season-1/325519 |archivedate=July 4, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> its [[The Amazing World of Gumball (season 6)|sixth season]] premiered on January 5, 2018. ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' revolves around the life of a 12-year-old cat named Gumball Watterson (Logan Grove, seasons 1 to 3; [[Jacob Hopkins]], season 3 to 5; Nicolas Cantu, rest of season 5 onwards) and his frequent shenanigans in the fictional American world of Elmore. Throughout the series, he interacts with characters such as his former pet, brother and best friend Darwin ([[Kwesi Boakye]], seasons 1 to 3; [[Terrell Ransom Jr.]], season 3 to 5; Donielle T. Hansley Jr, rest of season 5; Christian J. Simon, season 6 onwards), sister Anais (Kyla Rae Kowalewski), and parents Nicole and Richard ([[Teresa Gallagher]] and Dan Russell).\n\nBocquelet conceived ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' in 2007 while working as a development artist for [[Cartoon Network Studios Europe]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.turner.com/press_kits_detail.cfm?item_id=1298&presskit_id=239&press_section_id=2584 |title=Ben Bocquelet |publisher=[[Turner Broadcasting System]] |accessdate=October 19, 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDYqShEW?url=http://news.turner.com/press_kits_detail.cfm?item_id=1298&presskit_id=239&press_section_id=2584 |archivedate=November 18, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Daswani 2013\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.worldscreen.com/articles/display/40804|title=Ben Bocquelet & 'The Amazing World of Gumball'|journal=TV Kids|publisher=[[Mipcom]]|date=October 2013|pages=370\u201371|last=Daswani|first=Mansha|accessdate=November 18, 2013|url-access=subscription }}</ref> Having been asked by the network to pitch an idea for a new series for [[Adult Swim]], he took sketches of several unused characters he had created for commercials and started developing a concept for a new series based on them.<ref name=\"Animation\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/gumball-begins-reign-of-color |title=Gumball Begins Reign of Color |journal=[[Animation (magazine)|Animation]] |date=May 29, 2011 |accessdate=July 4, 2013 |last=Zahed |first=Ramin |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDYtMqr8?url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/gumball-begins-reign-of-color/ |archivedate=November 18, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> As Cartoon Network was heavily interested in \"family and school shows\" at the time, Bocquelet decided to make the series a kid series called ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' which was a combination of both.<ref name=\"Daswani 2013\"/><ref name=\"Animation\"/> He pitched the series to Daniel Lennard, vice president of Original Series and Development at [[Turner Broadcasting System|Turner Broadcasting]], who was impressed by the series' premise and ultimately greenlit its production.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thechildrensmediaconference.com/sessions/bafta-presents-the-amazing-world-of-gumball |title=BAFTA Presents: The Amazing World of Gumball |publisher=The Children's Media Conference |date=July 5, 2012 |accessdate=July 4, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141019230840/http://www.thechildrensmediaconference.com/sessions/bafta-presents-the-amazing-world-of-gumball/ |archivedate=October 19, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> The first series to be greenlit by Cartoon Network Studios Europe,<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://weblogs.variety.com/bltv/2011/05/cartoon-net-charms-with-clever-import-gumball.html |title=Cartoon Net Charms With Clever Import 'Gumball' |journal=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=May 3, 2011 |accessdate=October 19, 2013 |last=Lowry |first=Brian |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120527061324/http://weblogs.variety.com/bltv/2011/05/cartoon-net-charms-with-clever-import-gumball.html |archivedate=May 27, 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> it first aired on May 3, 2011 with the episode \"The DVD\", which was watched by 2.120 million viewers in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2011/05/04/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tnt-rides-nba-doubleheader-154112/cable_20110503 |title=Tuesday's Cable Ratings: TNT Rides NBA Doubleheader |publisher=[[The Futon Critic]] |date=May 4, 2011 |accessdate=July 3, 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6LDZ341Hd?url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/ratings/2011/05/04/tuesdays-cable-ratings-tnt-rides-nba-doubleheader-154112/cable_20110503/ |archivedate=November 18, 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn June 2, 2014, Cartoon Network announced that the series had been renewed a fourth and fifth season.<ref name=\"BarbaLachD'Amato2014\">{{cite press release | url=https://pressroom.turner.com/us/cartoon-network/amazing-world-gumball/cartoon-network-doubles-down-global-hit-series-amazing | title=Cartoon Network Doubles Down on Global Hit Series ''The Amazing World of Gumball'' | publisher=Turner Press Site | date=June 2, 2014 | accessdate=June 2, 2014 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140607000350/https://pressroom.turner.com/us/cartoon-network/amazing-world-gumball/cartoon-network-doubles-down-global-hit-series-amazing#.WYq8HCNOnJA | archive-date=June 7, 2014 | author1=Barba, Jessica | author2=Lach, Dawn | author3=D'Amato, Adrienne | location=Los Angeles and New York City}}</ref> Both seasons combined consisted of 40 eleven-minute episodes.<ref name=\"Marino2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.worldscreen.com/articles/display/2014-06-02-gumball-season-renewals |title=The Amazing World of Gumball Greenlit for 4th & 5th Seasons |publisher=World Screen |work=TV Kids |date=June 2, 2014 |accessdate=June 2, 2014 |author=Marino, Joel |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Q2kKYlJ6?url=http://www.worldscreen.com/articles/display/2014-06-02-gumball-season-renewals |archivedate=June 3, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn June 22, 2016, Cartoon Network renewed the series for a sixth season which would consist of 44 episodes.<ref name=\"awn.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.awn.com/news/amazing-world-gumball-renewed-season-six|title='Amazing World of Gumball' Renewed for Season Six|publisher=AWN|accessdate=July 5, 2016}}</ref> On September 6, 2016, [[Ben Bocquelet]] announced he would be departing production of ''Gumball'' upon completing the sixth season;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/benbocquelet/status/773562028489314309|title=Ben Bocquelet on Twitter|publisher=|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref> but production will continue without him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itechpost.com/articles/37923/20161008/the-amazing-world-of-gumball-creator-leaves-the-show-cartoon-network-to-continue-the-show-without-him.htm|title='Amazing World of Gumball' Creator Leaves The Show; Cartoon Network To Continue The Series Without Him?|first=iTech|last=Post|date=8 October 2016|publisher=|accessdate=1 January 2017}}</ref> However, on October 7, 2018, he retweeted an article stating that the sixth season will be the last. However, on October 2018, the author of that article made a follow up article clarifying that there could still be more seasons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.regularcapital.com/2018/10/more-seasons-of-the-amazing-world-of-gumball-is-still-a-possiblity/|title=More Seasons Of The Amazing World Of Gumball Is Still A Possibility|website=RegularCapital|date=October 12, 2018}}</ref>\nThe series is rated [[TV-Y7-FV]] in the [[United States]] (and has a PG certificate in the UK on all DVD releases) for comedic fantasy violence, mild to moderate suggestive content (including use of sexual innuendo), rude (often dark) humor, and scenes of danger.<ref>{{cite web|title=TV Parental Control|url=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/legal/ratings.html|publisher=[[Cartoon Network]]|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\nLater in November 2019, a six-episode miniseries titled \u201cDarwin's Yearbook\u201d was announced.<ref name=anim />\n\n==Series overview==\n\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| color0S    = #1E5994\n| link0S     = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Pilot (2008-2016)\n| episodes0S = 1\n| linkT0S    = Pilot\n| start0S    = {{Start date|2008|5|9}}\n| ends0S     = {{End date|2016|3|5}}\n\n| color1     = #5EC5C4\n| link1      = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 1 (2011\u201312)\n| episodes1  = 36\n| start1     = {{Start date|2011|5|3}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2012|3|13}}\n\n| color2     = #EDCC26\n| link2      = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 2 (2012\u201313)\n| episodes2  = 40\n| start2     = {{Start date|2012|8|7}}\n| end2       = {{End date|2013|12|3}}\n\n| color3     = #ACF16C\n| link3      = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 3 (2014\u201315)\n| episodes3  = 40\n| start3     = {{Start date|2014|6|5}}\n| end3       = {{End date|2015|8|6}}\n\n| color4     = #C869FB\n| link4      = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 4 (2015\u201316)\n| episodes4  = 40\n| start4     = {{Start date|2015|7|7}}\n| end4       = {{End date|2016|10|27}}\n\n| color5      = #FF5F5F\n| link5       = <includeonly>List of The Amazing World of Gumball episodes</includeonly>#Season 5 (2016\u201317)\n| episodes